   <p>Served with <corpname normal="United States. Army. Transportation Corps, 167th.">167th Co. Transportation Corps</corpname>, in the 
<geogname normal="Murmansk (Russia)">Murmansk</geogname> area.</p>
</bioghist>

<scopecontent encodinganalog="520">
   <p>The <genreform normal="Photograph albums.">album</genreform> contains ca. 350 <genreform normal="Photographs.">photographs</genreform>, 
including scenes of ports, camps in England and France, the countryside of Russia, <geogname normal="Murmansk (Russia)">Murmansk</geogname>, 
men on patrol and in camp, battle casualties, battle damage and construction on the railroad, Russian people, village scenes, fortifications, 
allied soldiers, airplanes,    repair of railroad cars, and the voyage home. These <genreform normal="Photographs.">photographs</genreform> 
are described in a printed <genreform normal="Lists.">list</genreform> distributed by <persname normal="Wilson, John E.">John E. Wilson.</persname>
   </p>

